post_cb({"28229453": {"ParentId": "28229382", "LastEditDate": "2015-01-30T05:05:53.050", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2015-01-30T04:55:28.953", "OwnerUserId": "862351", "LastEditorUserId": "862351", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "28229453", "Score": "8", "Body": "<p>You are looking at a border case - is a zero-sized array empty or not? Ignoring that specific question, the standard quote says that a general <code>std::array&lt;T,N&gt; arr</code>, on default construction, does not satisfy the post-condition <code>arr.empty()</code>. In fact, an <code>std::array&lt;T, N&gt;</code> is <code>empty()</code> only when <code>N==0</code>. And this definition is natural as well - <code>std::array&lt;T,N&gt;::size()</code> is a <code>constexpr</code> with value <code>N</code> and <code>empty()</code> should be synonymous with <code>size() == 0</code>.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2015-01-30T05:05:53.050"}, "28229382": {"CommentCount": "2", "ViewCount": "129", "OwnerDisplayName": "user3920237", "CreationDate": "2015-01-30T04:47:30.067", "LastActivityDate": "2015-01-30T05:05:53.050", "PostTypeId": "1", "AcceptedAnswerId": "28229453", "Title": "What does \"except that a default constructed array is not empty\" mean?", "Id": "28229382", "Score": "4", "Body": "<p>In N3337, I'm reading \u00a723.3.2.1/3 it states:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_28229382_28229382_0\">An <code>array</code> satisfies all of the requirements of a container and of a\n  reversible container (23.2), except that a default constructed <code>array</code>\n  object is not empty and that swap does not have constant complexity.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In \u00a723.2.1, Table 96 Container Requirements, it shows a default constructed object <code>X u;</code> where the post condition is <code>u.empty()</code>. Presumably then, the following:</p>\n<pre><code>std::array&lt;int, 0&gt; a;\n</code></pre>\n<p>should result with <code>a.empty()</code> outputting <code>1</code>, which it does. So what does \"empty\" mean here?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><stdarray>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_28229382_28229382_0": {"section_id": 776, "quality": 0.9473684210526315, "length": 18}}, "n3337": {"so_28229382_28229382_0": {"section_id": 763, "quality": 0.9473684210526315, "length": 18}}, "n4659": {"so_28229382_28229382_0": {"section_id": 837, "quality": 0.9473684210526315, "length": 18}}}});